        Behind on Your Mortgage and Considering Selling: Your Options Before Default in Queensland
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(240,236,228,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:54ch;">
        If you have missed repayments and are weighing a voluntary sale against waiting to see what the lender does, the window to act is narrower than most homeowners realise. Here is what the law allows and what actually protects your equity.
      </p>
